  "body": "### Issue\r\nWhen using `verify_merkle_branch`, the Merkle proof is against `state.latest_eth1_data.deposit_root`, not the `deposit_root` right after the deposit. The `Deposit` makers have to generate Merkle proof with `state.latest_eth1_data.deposit_root` locally.\r\n\r\n### Proposed solution\r\nThere might be various ways to generate Merkle proof and can be optimized so I'm not sure if we need to make it in-spec. But, at least it would be nice to add the format description of Merkle proof in the validator guide.\r\n",
